(BFA, BFB) said former chairman and chief executive Owsley Brown II, a member of the wine and liquor company's founding family, has died at the age of 69. The company said Brown, who began his career at Brown-Forman in 1968, died Monday night after a brief illness. Brown served as CEO from 1993 until 2005 and also served as chairman from 1995 to 2007.
